WEBVTT

00:00:02.500 --> 00:00:07.790
<i>You really never know
what life's going to throw at you.</i>

00:00:08.509 --> 00:00:13.088
<i>Never thought I'd end up
in a place like this with Kazumi.</i>

00:00:13.088 --> 00:00:14.629
Himari.

00:00:16.767 --> 00:00:18.509
Come here.

00:00:23.985 --> 00:00:28.519
Well then, let's end our friendship now.

00:00:34.175 --> 00:00:38.080
<i>Kazumi and I are best friends,</i>

00:00:38.080 --> 00:00:40.907
<i>so how did this happen?</i>

00:01:27.414 --> 00:01:31.500
[That morning]

00:01:37.900 --> 00:01:39.257
Himari.

00:01:41.172 --> 00:01:43.845
- Morning.
- Good morning, Kazumi.

00:01:45.022 --> 00:01:48.108
Hey, did you hear from Tomoya?

00:01:48.108 --> 00:01:51.611
Yeah! I was shocked. I had no idea.

00:01:51.611 --> 00:01:53.405
Did you know, Kazumi?

00:01:53.405 --> 00:01:55.699
He told me about six months ago,

00:01:55.699 --> 00:01:58.845
that he was thinking of marrying someone.

00:01:58.845 --> 00:02:00.693
What? You should've told me!

00:02:00.693 --> 00:02:04.708
Looks like he only told
the guys in our group.

00:02:04.708 --> 00:02:08.787
Besides, this is the kind of thing
you should hear from him directly.

00:02:08.787 --> 00:02:11.381
Why? We've known each other forever.

00:02:11.381 --> 00:02:13.374
It's like that sometimes.

00:02:14.794 --> 00:02:16.610
Anyway,

00:02:17.244 --> 00:02:19.056
what do we buy him?

00:02:19.056 --> 00:02:22.485
Should we all pitch in or buy separately?

00:02:22.485 --> 00:02:25.178
Hard to say.

00:02:25.924 --> 00:02:29.069
Let's hold a strategy meeting.

00:02:29.069 --> 00:02:30.289
You just want to drink.

00:02:30.289 --> 00:02:31.917
No, it's a strategy meeting.

00:02:31.917 --> 00:02:33.251
We drink every week.

00:02:33.251 --> 00:02:35.797
This is different from that.

00:02:35.797 --> 00:02:37.134
Yeah, yeah.

00:02:37.134 --> 00:02:39.538
Alright, then, the usual place tonight.

00:02:39.538 --> 00:02:42.266
Better make sure I get my work done early.

00:02:42.266 --> 00:02:45.172
Oh, I'll bring the manuscript today,

00:02:45.172 --> 00:02:47.212
so could you take a look at it early?

00:02:47.212 --> 00:02:49.330
The schedule's pretty tight.

00:02:52.134 --> 00:02:54.539
Fine, fine.

00:02:54.539 --> 00:02:56.296
Bring it over later.

00:02:57.347 --> 00:02:59.132
You're a lifesaver!

00:03:03.809 --> 00:03:06.632
[Vextos]

00:03:06.632 --> 00:03:08.358
Hojo.

00:03:08.358 --> 00:03:11.570
Could you do a final check
on tomorrow's press release?

00:03:11.570 --> 00:03:14.856
Thanks. Your speed is a great help.

00:03:21.699 --> 00:03:24.860
Yeah, looks good. No issues here.

00:03:24.860 --> 00:03:27.002
Got it, thank you.

00:03:27.002 --> 00:03:28.743
Hojo, is now a good time?

00:03:28.743 --> 00:03:30.447
Sure, go ahead.

00:03:30.447 --> 00:03:33.091
Here's the Fukuoka branch poster.

00:03:33.091 --> 00:03:36.637
The person in charge over there
wanted to emphasize local ties,

00:03:36.637 --> 00:03:39.848
so they used
handwritten messages and photos.

00:03:39.848 --> 00:03:41.729
I see.

00:03:41.729 --> 00:03:43.644
The design is approachable,

00:03:43.644 --> 00:03:47.389
and the large photos
make the local focus really clear.

00:03:47.389 --> 00:03:49.066
Thank you.

00:03:49.066 --> 00:03:51.851
But I can't approve it like this.

00:03:53.070 --> 00:03:57.981
The photos and messages are so large,
the key info isn't big enough.

00:03:57.981 --> 00:03:59.785
I understand the sentiment,

00:03:59.785 --> 00:04:03.080
but let's cut back
on the photos and messages.

00:04:03.080 --> 00:04:05.332
But isn't that too ordinary?

00:04:05.332 --> 00:04:07.638
Their feelings are what give it impact.

00:04:07.638 --> 00:04:09.277
Nihei.

00:04:09.277 --> 00:04:13.539
It's not about feelings.
It's about readability and understanding.

00:04:17.748 --> 00:04:19.629
Understood.

00:04:28.207 --> 00:04:30.520
Did I upset him?

00:04:30.520 --> 00:04:33.207
I'm not trying to shoot him down, but...

00:04:34.274 --> 00:04:36.604
It's hard to get that across.

00:04:37.745 --> 00:04:39.661
It's okay.

00:04:39.661 --> 00:04:43.533
I'm sure Nihei understands.

00:05:10.783 --> 00:05:12.434
Nihei.

00:05:13.102 --> 00:05:14.887
What's up?

00:05:14.887 --> 00:05:18.150
I figured you didn't like what he said.

00:05:18.150 --> 00:05:21.647
Well... I get what he was saying,

00:05:21.647 --> 00:05:24.661
but it feels like he's putting me in a box.

00:05:24.661 --> 00:05:26.997
Like a cog in a machine.

00:05:28.453 --> 00:05:31.790
Hojo is just being genuine.

00:05:31.790 --> 00:05:33.135
Genuine.

00:05:33.135 --> 00:05:34.459
Yeah.

00:05:34.459 --> 00:05:36.898
The branch office's feelings matter,

00:05:36.898 --> 00:05:39.005
but that's not the goal, right?

00:05:39.005 --> 00:05:43.157
Passion alone isn't enough to convince Hojo.

00:05:43.157 --> 00:05:47.305
We need something reliable,
yet fun to read for everyone.

00:05:47.305 --> 00:05:50.049
We need that kind of presentation.

00:05:51.268 --> 00:05:52.727
Presentation.

00:05:52.727 --> 00:05:55.179
Exactly. Presentation.

00:05:58.492 --> 00:06:01.561
Shibasaki, there you are.

00:06:02.453 --> 00:06:03.995
Wanna have lunch together?

00:06:03.995 --> 00:06:05.407
Sure.

00:06:05.407 --> 00:06:07.117
What about you?

00:06:07.117 --> 00:06:09.217
I'll have cup noodles at my desk.

00:06:09.217 --> 00:06:10.579
Got it.

00:06:10.579 --> 00:06:12.445
Too bad.

00:06:12.445 --> 00:06:14.907
- I'll go grab mine.
- Okay.

00:06:16.376 --> 00:06:18.957
What? You did it
four times with your boyfriend?

00:06:18.957 --> 00:06:20.038
Shush!

00:06:20.038 --> 00:06:21.799
Keep it down, Ando.

00:06:21.799 --> 00:06:23.457
Sorry.

00:06:24.160 --> 00:06:25.397
But four times is crazy.

00:06:25.397 --> 00:06:27.383
I mean, it can happen.

00:06:27.383 --> 00:06:28.672
Right, Shibasaki?

00:06:28.672 --> 00:06:31.007
<i>F-Four times?</i>

00:06:31.007 --> 00:06:33.102
<i>I-I'm jealous!</i>

00:06:33.102 --> 00:06:35.403
She gets like this sometimes.

00:06:35.403 --> 00:06:37.236
Shibasaki?

00:06:37.236 --> 00:06:39.882
Oh. Sorry.

00:06:39.882 --> 00:06:41.750
I was just so shocked.

00:06:41.750 --> 00:06:42.870
Yeah, right?

00:06:42.870 --> 00:06:44.613
Don't you get bored?

00:06:44.613 --> 00:06:46.437
That's where creativity comes in.

00:06:46.437 --> 00:06:49.986
You ask them what they're into,
and then you try it.

00:06:49.986 --> 00:06:51.580
So you tell each other your kinks?

00:06:51.580 --> 00:06:53.207
Well, I guess so.

00:06:53.207 --> 00:06:54.625
No way, I could never.

00:06:54.625 --> 00:06:56.326
But how else will they know?

00:06:56.326 --> 00:06:57.616
It's normal communication.

00:06:57.616 --> 00:06:59.457
I mean, sure, but...

00:06:59.457 --> 00:07:01.007
Could you, Shibasaki?

00:07:01.007 --> 00:07:05.423
<i>Being that open about yourself
is a dream come true.</i>

00:07:05.423 --> 00:07:06.823
She's doing it a lot today.

00:07:06.823 --> 00:07:08.929
Shibasaki!

00:07:08.929 --> 00:07:10.157
Huh?

00:07:11.032 --> 00:07:14.958
I don't think I could...

00:07:14.958 --> 00:07:19.183
I mean, what if they get turned off by it?

00:07:19.985 --> 00:07:23.351
So I admire people who can.

00:07:23.351 --> 00:07:25.757
It's like they're truly loved.

00:07:25.757 --> 00:07:27.284
Huh?

00:07:27.284 --> 00:07:29.119
That's surprising.

00:07:29.119 --> 00:07:32.664
I thought you were the more easy-going type.

00:07:32.664 --> 00:07:35.241
Don't you have a boyfriend now?

00:07:36.083 --> 00:07:38.953
Not since we broke up half a year ago.

00:07:40.589 --> 00:07:45.337
<i>All my breakups were mainly
due to mismatched sex lives.</i>

00:07:45.337 --> 00:07:49.117
<i>Being able to talk openly
about frequency and preferences...</i>

00:07:49.117 --> 00:07:51.549
<i>Honestly, I envy that.</i>

00:07:54.612 --> 00:07:56.104
But...

00:07:56.104 --> 00:07:59.478
I think I could say that stuff
to a friend instead of a boyfriend.

00:07:59.478 --> 00:08:00.817
I get that!

00:08:00.817 --> 00:08:03.092
With a boyfriend, you overthink things

00:08:03.092 --> 00:08:04.723
because you don't want to be disliked.

00:08:04.723 --> 00:08:08.038
If it's a friend,
even if you fight, you can just make up.

00:08:08.038 --> 00:08:11.277
But with a lover, worst case, it's over.

00:08:12.381 --> 00:08:14.277
<i>Aw, jeez.</i>

00:08:14.277 --> 00:08:17.356
<i>I wish there was someone out there</i>

00:08:17.356 --> 00:08:20.236
<i>who could satisfy both heart and body.</i>

00:08:24.248 --> 00:08:26.174
<i>Yeah, like that.</i>

00:08:26.174 --> 00:08:30.796
<i>I really like hands like that.</i>

00:08:43.363 --> 00:08:45.865
You dropped your handkerchief.

00:08:45.865 --> 00:08:50.158
Oh, thank you.

00:08:50.158 --> 00:08:53.190
<i>Oh, it's just Kazumi.</i>

00:08:55.197 --> 00:08:58.208
Wow, he's so easy on the eyes.

00:08:58.208 --> 00:08:59.668
Huh?

00:08:59.668 --> 00:09:03.254
He's handsome, refreshing, and nice, right?

00:09:03.254 --> 00:09:05.006
You think so?

00:09:05.006 --> 00:09:09.382
By the way, you two are friends, right?

00:09:09.382 --> 00:09:10.712
Yeah, I guess so.

00:09:10.712 --> 00:09:12.392
Friends since college.

00:09:12.392 --> 00:09:14.799
I just can't get rid of him.

00:09:15.575 --> 00:09:17.521
Is he really single?

00:09:17.521 --> 00:09:19.552
He looks like he'd be popular.

00:09:19.552 --> 00:09:22.223
Yeah, that's what I heard.

00:09:23.525 --> 00:09:27.195
Both of you are really surprising.

00:09:27.195 --> 00:09:30.398
Why don't you two have partners?

00:09:40.517 --> 00:09:41.626
Why?

00:09:41.626 --> 00:09:43.892
I'd like to know too!

00:09:43.892 --> 00:09:45.922
Blew a fuse, huh?

00:09:45.922 --> 00:09:49.801
All my friends from college
have gotten married one by one.

00:09:49.801 --> 00:09:55.691
In the end, you and I are all that are left.

00:09:55.691 --> 00:09:56.943
The leftovers, huh?

00:09:56.943 --> 00:10:00.353
Gosh, don't say it so bluntly!

00:10:00.353 --> 00:10:03.180
Okay, okay, sorry.

00:10:07.136 --> 00:10:10.277
Why are you so relaxed about this?

00:10:10.277 --> 00:10:14.018
I just don't think I need to rush.

00:10:14.018 --> 00:10:16.051
Why?

00:10:16.051 --> 00:10:20.448
Actually, you haven't had a girlfriend
for a while, have you, Kazumi?

00:10:21.082 --> 00:10:24.349
I probably haven't had one
since we met, Himari.

00:10:24.349 --> 00:10:25.730
Huh?

00:10:29.160 --> 00:10:32.850
Kazumi, do you have a sex drive?

00:10:32.850 --> 00:10:34.270
That's sudden.

00:10:34.270 --> 00:10:36.257
Of course I do. I'm a man.

00:10:36.257 --> 00:10:39.221
- Oh?
- You don't care?

00:10:41.167 --> 00:10:44.569
No, it's not that.

00:10:44.569 --> 00:10:48.642
It's just... with the way I look...

00:10:50.428 --> 00:10:53.384
If I say I have a sex drive...

00:10:53.384 --> 00:10:58.409
would it be a turn-off?

00:11:02.828 --> 00:11:05.201
I think that's awesome.

00:11:07.587 --> 00:11:10.400
It's the guy that's the problem.

00:11:12.425 --> 00:11:14.552
I'm being serious here!

00:11:14.552 --> 00:11:18.213
Things like the number of times,
frequency, and duration all matter.

00:11:18.213 --> 00:11:21.865
Yeah, if only you could know
your compatibility first.

00:11:21.865 --> 00:11:23.415
Exactly!

00:11:23.415 --> 00:11:27.141
What's a good way to figure it out?

00:11:28.747 --> 00:11:30.322
- I don't think there is one.
- Seriously?

00:11:30.322 --> 00:11:33.432
Hey! What was that for?

00:11:33.432 --> 00:11:34.886
Here.

00:11:38.718 --> 00:11:43.405
How do you even find
someone you're compatible with?

00:11:44.432 --> 00:11:48.711
Yeah, that's the tough part.

00:11:48.711 --> 00:11:51.121
Do you have anyone you like?

00:11:51.734 --> 00:11:54.801
I'm not really sure.

00:11:54.801 --> 00:11:56.886
You don't know yourself?

00:11:56.886 --> 00:11:59.973
Your own feelings
are the hardest to figure out.

00:12:02.139 --> 00:12:03.553
Hey!

00:12:14.611 --> 00:12:20.067
We used to vent like this in college too,
didn't we?

00:12:26.764 --> 00:12:28.152
I got dumped!

00:12:28.152 --> 00:12:31.129
Huh? But you two seemed so close.

00:12:31.129 --> 00:12:34.399
He said I wasn't what he expected.

00:12:34.399 --> 00:12:39.253
He wanted someone more mature and refined.

00:12:39.846 --> 00:12:43.292
I tried to be what he wanted, but...

00:12:43.292 --> 00:12:46.302
I see...

00:12:47.231 --> 00:12:51.649
Yeah, but I couldn't be myself
anymore anyway.

00:12:51.649 --> 00:12:53.651
Maybe it's a good thing.

00:12:53.651 --> 00:12:55.884
It was for the best.

00:12:55.884 --> 00:12:58.406
He knew nothing about you.

00:12:58.406 --> 00:13:02.410
You can be unexpectedly stubborn
and rough around the edges.

00:13:02.410 --> 00:13:05.099
Was that an insult?

00:13:05.099 --> 00:13:07.945
No way, I'm just stating the facts.

00:13:07.945 --> 00:13:09.677
Mean.

00:13:09.677 --> 00:13:10.915
What about you?

00:13:10.915 --> 00:13:13.943
Someone asked you out again, right?

00:13:13.943 --> 00:13:15.591
Oh, right.

00:13:16.575 --> 00:13:19.135
But I don't think I'll date them.

00:13:19.135 --> 00:13:21.095
Why?

00:13:21.095 --> 00:13:23.227
Same reason as before.

00:13:23.227 --> 00:13:28.802
They have expectations,
and then leave when you don't meet them.

00:13:31.356 --> 00:13:35.151
That's why you're great.
You don't expect anything from me.

00:13:35.151 --> 00:13:37.487
Nor do you want anything.

00:13:37.487 --> 00:13:40.439
It's so easy with you.

00:13:43.925 --> 00:13:47.898
When you're just friends,
it's so easy to talk about anything.

00:13:51.915 --> 00:13:56.464
If I put a letter in a bottle
and threw it into the river,

00:13:56.464 --> 00:14:03.346
would I meet a handsome,
kind, compatible guy from abroad?

00:14:03.346 --> 00:14:05.375
"I have a high sex drive. Is that okay?"

00:14:05.375 --> 00:14:06.462
Come on.

00:14:06.462 --> 00:14:09.784
But even if someone found it,
I still wouldn't think he was the one.

00:14:13.132 --> 00:14:14.640
You okay?

00:14:15.376 --> 00:14:17.232
Have some water.

00:14:17.232 --> 00:14:18.644
Thanks.

00:14:27.180 --> 00:14:32.020
Maybe I'll just put the letter
in this plastic bottle.

00:14:32.020 --> 00:14:34.694
Where's the romance in that?

00:14:34.694 --> 00:14:36.902
Hey, shut up.

00:15:02.639 --> 00:15:04.422
Sorry.

00:15:04.422 --> 00:15:06.540
I'll wipe that off.

00:15:16.689 --> 00:15:22.666
I think compatibility...
is hard to know until you give it a try.

00:15:24.093 --> 00:15:25.627
Huh?

00:15:27.513 --> 00:15:30.966
Yeah, that's true.

00:15:33.272 --> 00:15:37.431
Well then, wanna try with me?

00:15:40.037 --> 00:15:41.235
Huh?

00:15:41.235 --> 00:15:43.154
Just think about it.

00:15:43.154 --> 00:15:46.702
Starting with "Nice to meet you"
and "What's your hobby"

00:15:46.702 --> 00:15:48.609
sounds exhausting, right?

00:15:50.680 --> 00:15:54.615
I mean, sure, but...

00:15:55.416 --> 00:15:58.669
I already know your struggles, Himari,

00:15:58.669 --> 00:16:02.456
and I'm a good guy, as you can see.

00:16:04.349 --> 00:16:08.462
Hey, even as a joke,
that's not funny, Kazumi.

00:16:10.348 --> 00:16:12.174
I'm serious.

00:16:16.236 --> 00:16:17.352
Come here.

00:16:17.352 --> 00:16:19.225
Huh? Wait...

00:16:22.193 --> 00:16:27.621
<i>I knew that Kazumi
always shared how he really felt,</i>

00:16:27.621 --> 00:16:29.864
<i>and that made me happy.</i>

00:16:30.502 --> 00:16:35.164
<i>But I also sensed
that he was holding back somewhere,</i>

00:16:35.164 --> 00:16:38.951
<i>and there was a line he never crossed.</i>

00:16:41.063 --> 00:16:43.215
<i>And yet...</i>

00:16:54.902 --> 00:16:56.936
Hojo?

00:16:56.936 --> 00:16:58.983
What's wrong?

00:16:58.983 --> 00:17:01.859
I'm suddenly getting thirsty.

00:17:01.859 --> 00:17:04.059
Maybe I should go buy some water.

00:17:04.059 --> 00:17:05.853
They have water here.

00:17:07.447 --> 00:17:09.314
Oh, they do.

00:17:14.036 --> 00:17:15.487
Himari.

00:17:17.798 --> 00:17:19.416
Come here.

00:17:27.717 --> 00:17:32.254
Well then, let's end our friendship now.

00:17:50.375 --> 00:17:52.365
You were acting? What a turnoff.

00:17:52.365 --> 00:17:54.645
You're so loud.

00:17:57.574 --> 00:17:59.722
Kazumi.

00:17:59.722 --> 00:18:01.642
On second thought...

00:18:05.816 --> 00:18:08.123
Are you not okay with me?

00:18:09.333 --> 00:18:13.837
No, that's not it.

00:18:16.557 --> 00:18:18.383
Is it since we're friends?

00:18:24.484 --> 00:18:25.933
Are you scared?

00:18:33.068 --> 00:18:36.985
It must've been hard,
being rejected for who you are.

00:18:37.870 --> 00:18:40.239
There's no need to worry now.

00:18:42.879 --> 00:18:45.806
You can be whoever you are.

00:18:45.806 --> 00:18:47.781
I will always like you.

00:19:06.492 --> 00:19:09.220
How can you be so sure?

00:19:11.253 --> 00:19:13.162
Why do you think?

00:20:17.268 --> 00:20:18.874
Kazumi.

00:20:20.545 --> 00:20:25.079
Is it okay for us... to do this?

00:20:26.979 --> 00:20:29.982
Don't overthink it.

00:20:29.982 --> 00:20:32.048
Forget everything else...

00:20:33.538 --> 00:20:37.181
and just focus on what feels good.

00:20:42.664 --> 00:20:46.031
<i>Kazumi's words have a strange effect on me.</i>

00:20:46.684 --> 00:20:50.013
<i>They always make me feel at ease.</i>

00:20:52.546 --> 00:20:56.625
<i>Even though he never
goes into the actual details.</i>

00:20:59.594 --> 00:21:02.059
<i>His quiet breathing...</i>

00:21:10.136 --> 00:21:13.875
<i>The warmth of his chest
as I bury my face in it...</i>

00:21:14.675 --> 00:21:17.215
<i>The strength in his arms...</i>

00:21:18.037 --> 00:21:23.158
<i>The gentle warmth
of his skin enveloping me...</i>

00:21:24.161 --> 00:21:28.657
<i>It's all wrapping around me.</i>

00:21:31.700 --> 00:21:34.746
<i>It's not the usual Kazumi.</i>

00:21:35.607 --> 00:21:38.976
<i>Yet it feels so familiar.</i>

00:21:46.158 --> 00:21:51.680
<i>I sink deeper into that comfort.</i>

00:21:54.415 --> 00:21:57.995
<i>Deeper and deeper.</i>

00:22:08.371 --> 00:22:10.949
<i>I've done it now!</i>

00:22:13.085 --> 00:22:17.706
Well then, let's end our friendship now.

00:22:26.024 --> 00:22:29.593
Just focus on what feels good.

00:22:37.458 --> 00:22:39.368
What's wrong?

00:22:39.368 --> 00:22:40.900
Huh?

00:22:42.946 --> 00:22:45.068
It's nothing.

00:22:55.063 --> 00:23:01.502
<i>I crossed the line with my best friend!</i>

00:23:45.496 --> 00:23:48.582
I might not be able to look him in the eye.

00:23:48.582 --> 00:23:49.636
Don't run away.

00:23:49.636 --> 00:23:51.346
I won't let things end like that.

00:23:51.346 --> 00:23:53.266
I'm scared of things changing.

00:23:53.266 --> 00:23:56.894
Just what I expect
from the most popular girl in the company.

00:23:56.894 --> 00:23:58.120
Should we go back...

00:23:58.120 --> 00:24:00.067
To just being friends?